identifier: The Catena-X common ontology contains all domain-independent classes, attributes and relations.

definition_en: An entity that exists in a physical form.
synonyms_en: material entity, physical object, material object, concrete object, tangible, material, physical
is_disjoint_with: immaterial thing, action, event, organisation, person, place, process, product

definition_en: An entity that exists in a non-physical form.
example_en: idea, concept, information,  knowledge, feeling, domain, idea, concept, object, domain, plan
synonyms_en: immaterial entity, non-physical object, immaterial object, abstract object, intangible, immaterial, mental, non-material
is_disjoint_with: material thing, action, event, organisation, person, place, process, product

definition_en: An action is an activity or movement that is done in order to achieve a goal.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, event, organisation, person, place, process, product

definition_en: An event is something that happens at a given place and time.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, action, organisation, person, place, process, product

definition_en: A organization is a group of people who work together to achieve a common goal.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, action, event, person, place, process, product

definition_en: A person is a human being.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, action, event, organisation, place, process, product

definition_en: A place is a specific location.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, action, event, organisation, person, process, product

definition_en: A process is a set of activities that interact to produce a result; it has inputs and outputs, and a sequence of steps that in some way transform the inputs into the outputs.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, action, event, organisation, person, place, product

definition_en: A product is a good or service that is offered for sale.
is_disjoint_with: material thing, immaterial thing, action, event, organisation, person, place, process

definition_en: tangible, transferable product
intangible, not transferable product
A Business Partner is a legal entity that is part of the Catena-X network or that stands in a relevant relation to a Catena-X Business Partner.
The (long) Business Partner Number is a unique identifier following the pattern 'BPNL[0-9]{8}[A-Z]{4}'.
The (long) Business Partner Number Type describes strings following the pattern 'BPNL[0-9]{8}[A-Z]{4}'.
An Asset is any artifact that is provisioned/owned/attributed to some Catena-X Business Partner.
The provisioned by predicate connects assets to their providing Catena-X Business Partner.
A product that is ready for sale.
An intermediate product is a product that is used as a raw material or ingredient in the production of other products.
synonyms_en: intermediate goods, producer goods, semi-finished products

definition_en: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).
A specification is a document that outlines the requirements for a product, system, or service.
A string that identifies either a unique object or a unique class of objects.

example_en: global unique identifier (GUID), universally unique identifier (UUID)

definition_en: not source code
A number for identification.
A unique identifier assigned incrementally or sequentially to an item, to uniquely identify it.
"YYYY-MM-DD"
"hh:mm:ss"
The latitude of a location.
The longitude of a location.

synonyms_en: si system, international system of units

note_en: activity referred to a radionuclide (decays per unit time)
